I '''Justin Cronin''' (mibait 1962) metung yang Americanung talasulat libru. Mekasulat neng apat a nobela: ''Mary and O'Neil'' ampong ''The Summer Guest'', bukud kareng adwa kareng atlung libru ning vampire trilogy: ''[[The Passage (2010 nobela)|The Passage]]'' ampo ing ''[[The Twelve (novel)|The Twelve]]''. Sinambut neng [[Hemingway_Foundation/PEN_Award]], Stephen Crane Prize, ampong [[Whiting Writer's Award]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.randomhouse.com/author/results.pperl?authorid=6053 |title=Justin Cronin Author Bookshelf – Random House – Books – Audiobooks – Ebooks |publisher=Random House |accessdate=May 4, 2012}}</ref>

Mibait ya ampong meragul king New England i Cronin, miyari king [[Harvard University]] ampo king [[Iowa Writers’ Workshop]]. Tinuru yang makudtang pamanyulat He taught (''creative writing'') ampong "Author in-residence" ya king [[La Salle University]] king [[Philadelphia, PA]] manibat 1992 to 2003. Manuknangan ya king [[Houston]], Texas, kayabe ne ning asawa na ampong ának, nung nu ya sadyang propesor ning Ingles king   [[Rice University]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://enterthepassage.com/author/ |title=About the Author « The Passage by Justin Cronin |publisher=Enterthepassage.com |accessdate=May 4, 2012}}</ref>

